1
00:00:00,698 --> 00:00:03,735
The winner, Aichi Sendou!

2
00:00:03,735 --> 00:00:04,969
And there you have it.

3
00:00:04,969 --> 00:00:07,205
Team Q4 is moving
on to the main event.

4
00:00:07,205 --> 00:00:08,506
They'll be coming
back once again

5
00:00:08,506 --> 00:00:10,475
to face off
against Team Asteroid

6
00:00:10,475 --> 00:00:13,144
in the national
tournament final.

7
00:00:13,144 --> 00:00:15,012
Well, look at that.

8
00:00:15,012 --> 00:00:18,015
You won without
activating your Psyqualia.

9
00:00:18,015 --> 00:00:20,551
Are you foolish enough
to do that against me?

10
00:00:20,551 --> 00:00:34,599
♪

11
00:00:34,599 --> 00:00:37,402
It's time for us to learn
the true nature of your power.

12
00:00:37,402 --> 00:00:39,170
♪

13
00:00:39,170 --> 00:00:40,671
Hm.

14
00:00:40,671 --> 00:00:44,041
♪

15
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:45,710
Are you guys ready for
the toughest cardfights

16
00:00:45,710 --> 00:00:47,612
‐of your lives?
‐For sure!

17
00:00:47,612 --> 00:00:48,713
Hm.

18
00:00:48,713 --> 00:00:51,582
♪

19
00:00:51,582 --> 00:00:54,385
He made it this far with
nothing but his own strength.

20
00:00:54,385 --> 00:00:55,586
We're in the finals!

21
00:00:55,586 --> 00:00:57,588
Thanks to Alfred Early!

22
00:00:57,588 --> 00:00:59,290
Wasn't that crazy?

23
00:00:59,290 --> 00:01:01,959
Let's hope you didn't use up
all your luck on that draw.

24
00:01:01,959 --> 00:01:03,594
(chuckling)

25
00:01:03,594 --> 00:01:07,932
♪

26
00:01:10,134 --> 00:02:38,656
♪

27
00:02:42,193 --> 00:02:45,096
(wind howling)

28
00:02:51,636 --> 00:02:54,305
This is where it ended.

29
00:02:54,305 --> 00:02:57,108
You and I together with
our army of elite fighters

30
00:02:57,108 --> 00:03:01,012
can conquer the
world of Vanguard!

31
00:03:01,012 --> 00:03:03,214
‐No chance.
‐Huh?

32
00:03:03,214 --> 00:03:04,882
Get your deck.

33
00:03:04,882 --> 00:03:05,883
But‐‐

34
00:03:05,883 --> 00:03:08,252
I'll show you who's
the strongest right now.

35
00:03:08,252 --> 00:03:11,289
♪

36
00:03:11,289 --> 00:03:14,191
So, Kai, like my winning image?

37
00:03:14,191 --> 00:03:15,159
Ren,

38
00:03:15,159 --> 00:03:16,961
get me outta here!

39
00:03:16,961 --> 00:03:19,630
Rising from the shadows
to cut down my enemies.

40
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:20,531
Go!

41
00:03:20,531 --> 00:03:23,267
I'll destroy anyone
that interferes with me.

42
00:03:23,267 --> 00:03:24,969
(sinister chuckle)

43
00:03:24,969 --> 00:03:28,072
♪

44
00:03:28,072 --> 00:03:30,975
(exclaims)

45
00:03:30,975 --> 00:03:33,210
(grunting)

46
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:35,613
Ren!

47
00:03:35,613 --> 00:03:40,418
Kai...I...I've
gotten much stronger.

48
00:03:40,418 --> 00:03:42,553
♪

49
00:03:42,553 --> 00:03:43,421
Leaving?

50
00:03:43,421 --> 00:03:46,290
You can come
with me if you want.

51
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:49,594
I'll never turn my back on him.

52
00:03:49,594 --> 00:03:50,895
Yeah.

53
00:03:50,895 --> 00:03:55,933
♪

54
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:58,002
(gate rumbles open)

55
00:03:58,002 --> 00:04:08,546
♪

56
00:04:08,546 --> 00:04:10,281
I couldn't save him then.

57
00:04:10,281 --> 00:04:13,317
His newfound power
was overwhelming.

58
00:04:13,317 --> 00:04:16,320
Losing my friend like that was
too difficult for me to bear.

59
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:20,825
So I did the only thing
that made sense at the time:

60
00:04:20,825 --> 00:04:23,027
I ran away.

61
00:04:23,027 --> 00:04:27,264
Still, I'm not the same
person I used to be.

62
00:04:27,264 --> 00:04:29,066
You know it, Aichi.

63
00:04:29,066 --> 00:04:32,303
This isn't what you
pictured for our battle.

64
00:04:32,303 --> 00:04:36,040
It's true, I wanted to be
your equal and friend.

65
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:42,613
♪

66
00:04:42,613 --> 00:04:45,449
Aichi almost lost
himself to Psyqualia.

67
00:04:45,449 --> 00:04:48,719
But knowing what I know now,
I was able to stop him.

68
00:04:48,719 --> 00:04:50,221
Which means...

69
00:04:50,221 --> 00:04:53,090
♪

70
00:04:53,090 --> 00:04:55,393
This time, I won't fail.

71
00:04:55,393 --> 00:05:07,638
♪

72
00:05:07,638 --> 00:05:09,607
Tetsu.

73
00:05:09,607 --> 00:05:34,632
♪

74
00:05:37,468 --> 00:05:39,737
Hm...

75
00:05:39,737 --> 00:05:40,838
(exclaims)

76
00:05:40,838 --> 00:05:41,739
(thud)

77
00:05:44,308 --> 00:05:48,145
Well, it's about time.

78
00:05:48,145 --> 00:05:50,881
I knew after your team
made the finals you'd come.

79
00:05:50,881 --> 00:05:52,550
Do you know why I've come back?

80
00:05:52,550 --> 00:05:53,417
Yeah.

81
00:05:53,417 --> 00:05:56,087
You want to rob me
of my powers, right?

82
00:05:56,087 --> 00:05:58,989
Just like you did to Aichi.

83
00:05:58,989 --> 00:06:00,891
(whirring)

84
00:06:03,427 --> 00:06:04,595
Poor kid.

85
00:06:04,595 --> 00:06:06,163
Thanks to the way you've
messed with his head,

86
00:06:06,163 --> 00:06:08,365
he has this idea that
the best thing for him to do

87
00:06:08,365 --> 00:06:12,036
is deny himself the amazing
gift that he was given.

88
00:06:12,036 --> 00:06:13,571
What's your problem?

89
00:06:13,571 --> 00:06:18,476
Are you jealous that
he has it and you don't, hm?

90
00:06:18,476 --> 00:06:23,013
I didn't realize your ego
was so easily damaged.

91
00:06:23,013 --> 00:06:26,117
I watched as that power
changed you for the worse.

92
00:06:26,117 --> 00:06:28,085
Relying on it has made you
forget the whole reason

93
00:06:28,085 --> 00:06:31,689
we started playing Vanguard
in the first place.

94
00:06:31,689 --> 00:06:36,460
All you play for now is your
obsession with your own image.

95
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:38,763
Do you even remember
what it was like?

96
00:06:38,763 --> 00:06:42,066
cardfighting because
it was what you loved to do?

97
00:06:42,066 --> 00:06:44,301
Easy, now.

98
00:06:44,301 --> 00:06:47,505
I'll never forget the past
we shared as teammates.

99
00:06:47,505 --> 00:06:51,308
We sure had some
good times together.

100
00:06:51,308 --> 00:06:54,612
But then, you ruined everything,

101
00:06:54,612 --> 00:06:57,047
Kai.

102
00:06:57,047 --> 00:07:00,484
You were the one that
turned your back on us.

103
00:07:00,484 --> 00:07:02,987
I thought I was your friend.

104
00:07:02,987 --> 00:07:07,892
That all ended the day
I became stronger than you.

105
00:07:07,892 --> 00:07:09,994
The three of us
built Team Asteroid.

106
00:07:09,994 --> 00:07:12,296
We dreamed of playing
in the national tournament,

107
00:07:12,296 --> 00:07:14,265
though none of us
were ready for it.

108
00:07:14,265 --> 00:07:15,900
I didn't care
if we were the best,

109
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:18,135
I wanted to spend
time with you guys.

110
00:07:18,135 --> 00:07:21,972
♪

111
00:07:21,972 --> 00:07:23,607
Yet it wasn't to be.

112
00:07:23,607 --> 00:07:27,912
You became fixated on getting
our team past the regionals.

113
00:07:27,912 --> 00:07:31,215
I felt bad, it obviously
meant a lot to you.

114
00:07:31,215 --> 00:07:34,718
♪

115
00:07:34,718 --> 00:07:36,987
I decided I needed
to step it up,

116
00:07:36,987 --> 00:07:39,657
for you and Tetsu, my teammates.

117
00:07:39,657 --> 00:07:42,059
I had to improve because
that's what you wanted

118
00:07:42,059 --> 00:07:43,127
for the team.

119
00:07:43,127 --> 00:07:45,796
We were trying to get
to the national tournament.

120
00:07:45,796 --> 00:07:48,799
And if we won there,
then we'd always be together

121
00:07:48,799 --> 00:07:51,702
if we had the strength to do so.

122
00:07:51,702 --> 00:07:52,937
Then...

123
00:07:52,937 --> 00:07:55,840
♪

124
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:58,142
I need to get stronger!

125
00:07:58,142 --> 00:08:00,344
(lightning crashes)

126
00:08:00,344 --> 00:08:04,081
♪

127
00:08:04,081 --> 00:08:06,417
My friends are counting on me.

128
00:08:06,417 --> 00:08:08,452
I have to get better.

129
00:08:08,452 --> 00:08:12,423
If I don't get stronger,
my team will...

130
00:08:12,423 --> 00:08:14,325
(lightning crashes)

131
00:08:16,327 --> 00:08:18,562
Huh?

132
00:08:18,562 --> 00:08:21,365
♪

133
00:08:21,365 --> 00:08:22,733
(gasps)

134
00:08:22,733 --> 00:08:28,405
♪

135
00:08:28,405 --> 00:08:32,977
I hear it‐‐the cards
are talking to me.

136
00:08:32,977 --> 00:08:37,348
I knew I'd found something
special right away.

137
00:08:37,348 --> 00:08:40,517
More possibilities
than I'd ever imagined.

138
00:08:40,517 --> 00:08:43,320
And it was so easy.

139
00:08:44,622 --> 00:08:48,292
The only thing I had
to do was listen to them.

140
00:08:48,292 --> 00:08:50,027
They told me
which unit was needed

141
00:08:50,027 --> 00:08:53,063
for me to win my next match.

142
00:08:53,063 --> 00:08:57,234
My deck itself was
a path to victory.

143
00:08:57,234 --> 00:09:01,472
I attained real power
for the sake of your goals.

144
00:09:01,472 --> 00:09:03,540
I was excited to show you guys.

145
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:08,545
My best friends needed
to share in my discovery.

146
00:09:08,545 --> 00:09:11,115
Though Tetsu's fear
was plain to see,

147
00:09:11,115 --> 00:09:14,451
he continued to stand by me.

148
00:09:14,451 --> 00:09:16,420
But not you.

149
00:09:16,420 --> 00:09:18,923
Our friendship wasn't
worth that much.

150
00:09:18,923 --> 00:09:22,693
My new power was supposed
to help us realize our dreams.

151
00:09:22,693 --> 00:09:25,029
Tell me, why did you run?

152
00:09:25,029 --> 00:09:26,797
Why did you betray us?

153
00:09:26,797 --> 00:09:35,439
♪

154
00:09:35,439 --> 00:09:36,941
(gasps)

155
00:09:36,941 --> 00:09:47,251
♪

156
00:09:47,251 --> 00:09:48,886
(growling)

157
00:09:48,886 --> 00:09:50,988
How dare you!

158
00:09:50,988 --> 00:09:53,657
(echoing)
Kai!

159
00:09:53,657 --> 00:09:59,797
♪

160
00:09:59,797 --> 00:10:02,499
I became consumed
with hating you.

161
00:10:02,499 --> 00:10:05,836
In every fight I won,
every player I defeated,

162
00:10:05,836 --> 00:10:09,940
in my mind, I was
always beating you.

163
00:10:09,940 --> 00:10:11,976
Psyqualia was a gift,

164
00:10:11,976 --> 00:10:15,412
and it was my job
to share it with the world.

165
00:10:15,412 --> 00:10:21,085
Then, even fools like
you would see the truth.

166
00:10:21,085 --> 00:10:22,686
(chuckling)

167
00:10:22,686 --> 00:10:28,058
♪

168
00:10:28,058 --> 00:10:29,460
And now,

169
00:10:29,460 --> 00:10:31,328
the world's top players
have flocked here

170
00:10:31,328 --> 00:10:33,664
just for the chance
to play beside me.

171
00:10:33,664 --> 00:10:37,234
I have over 500 hopeful
cardfighters at my disposal.

172
00:10:40,104 --> 00:10:42,873
I wish you knew
what it felt like.

173
00:10:42,873 --> 00:10:45,209
The power surging
through my veins,

174
00:10:45,209 --> 00:10:47,578
sharpening my skills.

175
00:10:47,578 --> 00:10:48,912
You've got to admit it,
it's pretty funny

176
00:10:48,912 --> 00:10:51,215
we used to dream about
going to nationals.

177
00:10:51,215 --> 00:10:54,952
The players there aren't
even worth my time anymore.

178
00:10:54,952 --> 00:10:57,588
And I couldn't have
done it without you.

179
00:10:57,588 --> 00:10:58,622
(growls)

180
00:10:58,622 --> 00:11:00,057
Hating you made it
possible for me

181
00:11:00,057 --> 00:11:02,326
to focus my wild ability.

182
00:11:02,326 --> 00:11:03,494
Take a look at me now.

183
00:11:03,494 --> 00:11:06,663
I'm unparalleled by
anyone else on the planet.

184
00:11:06,663 --> 00:11:09,299
Winning the nationals
without even trying.

185
00:11:09,299 --> 00:11:11,535
With Team Asteroid,

186
00:11:11,535 --> 00:11:14,571
there's no limit to the things
I'll be able to accomplish.

187
00:11:14,571 --> 00:11:16,874
Well, where do we go from here?

188
00:11:16,874 --> 00:11:18,042
I know.

189
00:11:18,042 --> 00:11:20,344
Maybe I'll take over
the world next.

190
00:11:20,344 --> 00:11:23,380
♪

191
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:25,949
I didn't come for
a lecture, Ren.

192
00:11:25,949 --> 00:11:27,418
(chuckles)

193
00:11:27,418 --> 00:11:29,920
I came 'cause I'm finally
strong enough to beat you.

194
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:32,656
I'm gonna bring back
the person you used to be.

195
00:11:32,656 --> 00:11:35,793
I swear it to you.

196
00:11:35,793 --> 00:11:37,761
The person I used to be?

197
00:11:37,761 --> 00:11:39,863
I'm afraid that's not possible.

198
00:11:39,863 --> 00:11:41,398
Sorry to be the one
to tell you this,

199
00:11:41,398 --> 00:11:43,267
but the guy I
used to be is gone

200
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:46,070
and the world's top
cardfighter remains.

201
00:11:46,070 --> 00:11:47,805
Then again, you wouldn't
have come without something

202
00:11:47,805 --> 00:11:49,339
up your sleeve,

203
00:11:49,339 --> 00:11:51,108
and that's perfectly fine by me.

204
00:11:51,108 --> 00:11:53,811
You'll need all
the help you can get.

205
00:11:53,811 --> 00:11:55,779
I'm gonna destroy you
with the power

206
00:11:55,779 --> 00:11:57,781
that you hate so much.

207
00:11:57,781 --> 00:12:00,584
♪

208
00:12:00,584 --> 00:12:02,419
No.

209
00:12:02,419 --> 00:12:06,957
♪

210
00:12:10,694 --> 00:12:14,631
♪

211
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,601
‐Tetsu?
‐Huh?

212
00:12:17,601 --> 00:12:21,538
Hang on to this for me.

213
00:12:21,538 --> 00:12:22,840
Hm.

214
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,541
I'd rather just use the glove.

215
00:12:24,541 --> 00:12:26,543
Those helmets are way too bulky.

216
00:12:26,543 --> 00:12:28,479
So, are you ready?

217
00:12:28,479 --> 00:12:31,148
I wish it didn't have
to go down like this.

218
00:12:34,485 --> 00:12:36,120
We'll be watching
this fight too...

219
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,721
if it's okay with you boys.

220
00:12:37,721 --> 00:12:39,056
Hm?

221
00:12:39,056 --> 00:12:42,860
♪

222
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:44,995
What are they doing here?

223
00:12:44,995 --> 00:12:47,164
They're my biggest fans.

224
00:12:47,164 --> 00:12:48,232
What's the problem?

225
00:12:48,232 --> 00:12:50,100
Don't tell me you're
afraid of losing a battle

226
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:52,302
in front of your
favorite pop group.

227
00:12:52,302 --> 00:12:55,472
♪

228
00:12:55,472 --> 00:12:57,674
Hm?

229
00:12:57,674 --> 00:13:00,944
Took long enough.

230
00:13:00,944 --> 00:13:01,778
Hm?

231
00:13:01,778 --> 00:13:03,413
Hey, Kai.

232
00:13:03,413 --> 00:13:05,149
And Ren too?

233
00:13:05,149 --> 00:13:06,783
Aichi!

234
00:13:06,783 --> 00:13:08,085
Huh!

235
00:13:08,085 --> 00:13:09,853
Uh...you see...

236
00:13:09,853 --> 00:13:12,589
Kourin asked me to come down.

237
00:13:12,589 --> 00:13:15,726
I think he's earned the right
to watch what happens today.

238
00:13:15,726 --> 00:13:16,927
(chuckles)

239
00:13:16,927 --> 00:13:18,295
Yeah, he sure has.

240
00:13:18,295 --> 00:13:20,197
Isn't it wonderful how
people flock together

241
00:13:20,197 --> 00:13:21,999
to witness me play?

242
00:13:21,999 --> 00:13:25,702
Makes me feel all
warm and fuzzy inside.

243
00:13:25,702 --> 00:13:26,670
Listen up.

244
00:13:26,670 --> 00:13:28,272
If you're gonna stick around,

245
00:13:28,272 --> 00:13:30,407
then study the way he plays.

246
00:13:30,407 --> 00:13:31,909
You guys are gonna fight?

247
00:13:31,909 --> 00:13:35,546
♪

248
00:13:35,546 --> 00:13:38,782
What's this about?

249
00:13:38,782 --> 00:13:40,117
It's time.

250
00:13:40,117 --> 00:13:41,818
The training I've done
in the last few years

251
00:13:41,818 --> 00:13:43,854
has been for this moment.

252
00:13:43,854 --> 00:13:46,056
I guess you must be curious

253
00:13:46,056 --> 00:13:48,492
about what my power
is really like.

254
00:13:48,492 --> 00:13:51,295
Hardly, it doesn't matter.

255
00:13:51,295 --> 00:13:55,399
You say that, Kai,
but you know what I think?

256
00:13:55,399 --> 00:13:57,601
You should see it for yourself.

257
00:13:57,601 --> 00:13:59,336
♪

258
00:13:59,336 --> 00:14:00,904
Huh?

259
00:14:00,904 --> 00:14:07,010
♪

260
00:14:07,010 --> 00:14:09,980
No way!

261
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:11,448
I've been here.

262
00:14:11,448 --> 00:14:13,150
His Psyqualia.

263
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:14,818
Hm!

264
00:14:14,818 --> 00:14:16,787
(laughing)

265
00:14:16,787 --> 00:14:23,393
♪

266
00:14:23,393 --> 00:14:24,861
Is it clear?

267
00:14:24,861 --> 00:14:26,763
My winning image.

268
00:14:26,763 --> 00:14:29,466
So it's...that unit.

269
00:14:29,466 --> 00:14:33,470
♪

270
00:14:33,470 --> 00:14:36,673
Who cares about your power?

271
00:14:36,673 --> 00:14:38,575
You'll soon realize,

272
00:14:38,575 --> 00:14:40,177
no matter how strong you get,

273
00:14:40,177 --> 00:14:43,747
you're never gonna be able to
play at the level I've reached.

274
00:14:43,747 --> 00:14:45,249
(sinister chuckle)

275
00:14:45,249 --> 00:14:56,260
♪

276
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:59,062
Stand up, the Vanguard!

277
00:14:59,062 --> 00:15:14,144
♪

278
00:15:14,144 --> 00:15:15,445
Draw.

279
00:15:15,445 --> 00:15:18,849
I ride Bahr...

280
00:15:18,849 --> 00:15:20,817
and move Conroe.

281
00:15:20,817 --> 00:15:22,452
I draw.

282
00:15:22,452 --> 00:15:25,055
I ride Blaster Javelin.

283
00:15:25,055 --> 00:15:26,456
(roar)

284
00:15:26,456 --> 00:15:29,493
♪

285
00:15:29,493 --> 00:15:31,928
I call‐‐and attack!

286
00:15:31,928 --> 00:15:38,468
♪

287
00:15:38,468 --> 00:15:42,072
Javelin, let's go.

288
00:15:42,072 --> 00:15:43,774
(roaring)

289
00:15:43,774 --> 00:15:47,244
♪

290
00:15:47,244 --> 00:15:50,547
I ride Dragon Knight, Nehalem!

291
00:15:50,547 --> 00:15:53,550
♪

292
00:15:53,550 --> 00:15:57,054
Burning Horn Dragon and
Aermo to the rear guard.

293
00:15:57,054 --> 00:15:59,022
♪

294
00:15:59,022 --> 00:16:00,557
With Conroe's support,

295
00:16:00,557 --> 00:16:03,493
Burning Horn Dragon
attacks Gururubau.

296
00:16:03,493 --> 00:16:08,398
♪

297
00:16:08,398 --> 00:16:10,534
Gururubau!

298
00:16:10,534 --> 00:16:12,536
♪

299
00:16:12,536 --> 00:16:14,905
Aermo supports an
attack from Nehalem.

300
00:16:14,905 --> 00:16:19,543
♪

301
00:16:19,543 --> 00:16:22,913
Checking the trigger...

302
00:16:22,913 --> 00:16:24,981
(yells)

303
00:16:24,981 --> 00:16:26,750
Perfect.

304
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,852
It seems the cards
favor me again.

305
00:16:28,852 --> 00:16:31,855
Blaster Javelin
gains 5,000 power.

306
00:16:31,855 --> 00:16:33,190
I draw.

307
00:16:33,190 --> 00:16:38,495
♪

308
00:16:38,495 --> 00:16:39,896
I never thought
I'd see the day

309
00:16:39,896 --> 00:16:42,666
when the three of us
were back together again.

310
00:16:42,666 --> 00:16:45,769
But things have changed
a lot since then, Kai.

311
00:16:45,769 --> 00:16:48,338
You have no chance of winning.

312
00:16:48,338 --> 00:16:50,340
Ren's power level

313
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:51,875
is terrifying.

314
00:16:53,910 --> 00:16:55,912
I ride.

315
00:16:55,912 --> 00:16:59,349
Blaster Dark!

316
00:16:59,349 --> 00:17:00,684
Call!

317
00:17:00,684 --> 00:17:04,488
♪

318
00:17:04,488 --> 00:17:07,858
Nemain's counterblast.

319
00:17:07,858 --> 00:17:10,227
DonnerSchlag attacks.

320
00:17:10,227 --> 00:17:11,795
Bahr will guard.

321
00:17:11,795 --> 00:17:14,297
Next, I attack
with Blaster Dark.

322
00:17:14,297 --> 00:17:16,199
I don't guard.

323
00:17:16,199 --> 00:17:17,968
♪

324
00:17:17,968 --> 00:17:20,170
Looks like a critical trigger.

325
00:17:20,170 --> 00:17:21,872
(sounds of struggle)

326
00:17:21,872 --> 00:17:24,307
♪

327
00:17:24,307 --> 00:17:26,042
Heal trigger activates.

328
00:17:26,042 --> 00:17:27,811
The power to Nehalem,

329
00:17:27,811 --> 00:17:30,580
and I heal one point of damage.

330
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:31,848
Face it, Kai.

331
00:17:31,848 --> 00:17:34,484
You're afraid because
you don't understand it.

332
00:17:34,484 --> 00:17:37,087
♪

333
00:17:37,087 --> 00:17:39,289
This'll be just like last time.

334
00:17:39,289 --> 00:17:41,858
Your fear will betray you.

335
00:17:41,858 --> 00:17:44,694
In the end, you'll run away.

336
00:17:44,694 --> 00:17:47,130
Not a chance.

337
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:50,167
I won't run!

338
00:17:50,167 --> 00:17:51,768
But, Kai...

339
00:17:51,768 --> 00:17:53,603
♪

340
00:17:53,603 --> 00:17:57,340
I ride Dragonic Overlord!

341
00:17:57,340 --> 00:17:59,543
♪

342
00:17:59,543 --> 00:18:01,445
I call Berserk Dragon.

343
00:18:01,445 --> 00:18:03,814
♪

344
00:18:03,814 --> 00:18:06,283
Counterblast.

345
00:18:06,283 --> 00:18:09,052
I banish Karen.

346
00:18:09,052 --> 00:18:12,055
I'll have Berserk
Dragon attack Nemain.

347
00:18:12,055 --> 00:18:15,292
♪

348
00:18:15,292 --> 00:18:18,428
(screaming)

349
00:18:18,428 --> 00:18:23,600
With Aermo's support,
Overlord attacks.

350
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,435
(roaring)

351
00:18:25,435 --> 00:18:27,304
♪

352
00:18:27,304 --> 00:18:29,606
I don't guard.

353
00:18:29,606 --> 00:18:31,608
Checking the twin drive.

354
00:18:31,608 --> 00:18:35,846
♪

355
00:18:35,846 --> 00:18:38,281
There‐‐a critical trigger.

356
00:18:38,281 --> 00:18:40,484
Overlord gains
the critical effect,

357
00:18:40,484 --> 00:18:43,453
and the 5,000 power
goes to Burning Horn.

358
00:18:43,453 --> 00:18:52,095
♪

359
00:18:52,095 --> 00:18:53,997
Aermo's skill.

360
00:18:53,997 --> 00:18:57,667
♪

361
00:18:57,667 --> 00:19:00,337
With Conroe's support...

362
00:19:00,337 --> 00:19:03,406
Burning Horn attacks.

363
00:19:03,406 --> 00:19:05,575
Burning Horn's ability?

364
00:19:05,575 --> 00:19:06,610
As long as my Vanguard

365
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:08,612
has the word
"Overlord" in its name,

366
00:19:08,612 --> 00:19:12,415
this unit gets
an extra 3,000 power.

367
00:19:12,415 --> 00:19:16,119
♪

368
00:19:16,119 --> 00:19:18,255
(explosion)

369
00:19:18,255 --> 00:19:21,024
♪

370
00:19:21,024 --> 00:19:23,159
Well, well, a heal trigger.

371
00:19:23,159 --> 00:19:25,095
The power boost goes
to Blaster Dark,

372
00:19:25,095 --> 00:19:27,898
and I heal one point of damage.

373
00:19:27,898 --> 00:19:29,499
That's so sad.

374
00:19:29,499 --> 00:19:30,600
Huh?

375
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,769
Fighting is the only way
they can talk to each other.

376
00:19:32,769 --> 00:19:35,906
This is what true rivals are.

377
00:19:35,906 --> 00:19:38,241
No kidding.

378
00:19:38,241 --> 00:19:40,644
I stand and draw.

379
00:19:40,644 --> 00:19:43,780
Surely you must have
guessed what's coming next.

380
00:19:43,780 --> 00:19:45,482
Hm.

381
00:19:45,482 --> 00:19:48,351
I ride Phantom Blaster Dragon.

382
00:19:48,351 --> 00:19:50,220
(yells)

383
00:19:50,220 --> 00:19:58,695
♪

384
00:19:58,695 --> 00:20:00,063
I call.

385
00:20:00,063 --> 00:20:03,700
♪

386
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:05,535
DonnerSchlag's coming in.

387
00:20:05,535 --> 00:20:07,170
Kimnara will guard.

388
00:20:07,170 --> 00:20:09,406
And now, with support
from Apocalypse,

389
00:20:09,406 --> 00:20:13,209
Phantom Blaster
Dragon takes aim.

390
00:20:13,209 --> 00:20:15,679
Apocalypse's Soul Blast!

391
00:20:15,679 --> 00:20:18,915
Since the boosted unit
has "Blaster" in its name,

392
00:20:18,915 --> 00:20:21,751
this attack gets
another 6,000 power.

393
00:20:21,751 --> 00:20:25,288
♪

394
00:20:25,288 --> 00:20:26,456
No guard.

395
00:20:26,456 --> 00:20:28,024
Check the drive trigger.

396
00:20:28,024 --> 00:20:31,227
♪

397
00:20:31,227 --> 00:20:33,363
The cards favor me.

398
00:20:33,363 --> 00:20:36,166
The power boost
goes to Fatalita.

399
00:20:36,166 --> 00:20:37,834
And then I draw.

400
00:20:37,834 --> 00:20:40,837
♪

401
00:20:40,837 --> 00:20:43,173
Got my own draw trigger.

402
00:20:43,173 --> 00:20:45,208
The power goes to Overlord.

403
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:55,185
♪

404
00:20:55,185 --> 00:20:58,054
Boosted by Karen,
Fatalita attacks!

405
00:20:58,054 --> 00:20:59,990
Tahr will stop you.

406
00:20:59,990 --> 00:21:03,259
I've never seen a battle
with this much animosity.

407
00:21:03,259 --> 00:21:05,261
♪

408
00:21:05,261 --> 00:21:06,763
As I expected,

409
00:21:06,763 --> 00:21:09,199
you've lost sight of the reason
we started playing this game

410
00:21:09,199 --> 00:21:10,367
in the first place,

411
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:12,569
and I'm going to remind you.

412
00:21:12,569 --> 00:21:13,637
By defeating you here,

413
00:21:13,637 --> 00:21:16,706
I'll be able to bring back
the Ren I once knew.

414
00:21:16,706 --> 00:21:18,708
Seriously?

415
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:22,245
The Ren you used to know
is but a shadow of the past.

416
00:21:22,245 --> 00:21:24,514
You keep going on and on
about how you've come

417
00:21:24,514 --> 00:21:27,984
to save me from whatever
it is that I've become.

418
00:21:27,984 --> 00:21:30,954
Why can't you see it's futile?

419
00:21:30,954 --> 00:21:34,224
‐I've got this.
‐Hm?

420
00:21:34,224 --> 00:21:35,992
This is the card that
I'll use to defeat you

421
00:21:35,992 --> 00:21:38,461
once and for all.

422
00:21:38,461 --> 00:21:40,096
(growls)

423
00:21:40,096 --> 00:21:41,598
Harbinger of Destruction,

424
00:21:41,598 --> 00:21:44,668
spread your ravaging flames
across this battlefield...

425
00:21:44,668 --> 00:21:46,603
and rise from the ashes.

426
00:21:46,603 --> 00:21:49,439
The Overlord has reached
his ultimate form!

427
00:21:49,439 --> 00:21:52,008
Cross Ride!

428
00:21:52,008 --> 00:21:56,179
Dragonic Overlord, the end!

429
00:21:56,179 --> 00:22:00,316
♪

430
00:22:00,316 --> 00:22:03,520
I've never seen that
used before in my life.

431
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:08,558
♪

432
00:22:08,558 --> 00:22:10,193
(growls)

433
00:22:10,193 --> 00:22:11,661
♪

434
00:22:11,661 --> 00:22:13,730
What do you think of
my Dragonic Overlord's

435
00:22:13,730 --> 00:22:15,465
final evolution?

436
00:22:15,465 --> 00:22:17,834
Its true form.

437
00:22:17,834 --> 00:22:18,968
All right.

438
00:22:18,968 --> 00:22:21,971
Let's see if we can't
find the old you, huh?

439
00:22:26,609 --> 00:23:55,932
♪

440
00:24:00,336 --> 00:24:01,437
Cross Ride?

441
00:24:01,437 --> 00:24:02,672
Wow, as soon as
I thought I knew

442
00:24:02,672 --> 00:24:04,741
everything about this game.

443
00:24:04,741 --> 00:24:06,509
Aichi, watch closely.

444
00:24:06,509 --> 00:24:08,144
This fight is important.

445
00:24:08,144 --> 00:24:11,181
I'm gonna bring him back
just like I did you.

446
00:24:11,181 --> 00:24:12,348
Give it up, Kai.

447
00:24:12,348 --> 00:24:13,817
In the face of Psyqualia,

448
00:24:13,817 --> 00:24:16,352
even your best efforts
will be wasted.

449
00:24:16,352 --> 00:24:18,822
If Ren knows how this
is going to unfold,

450
00:24:18,822 --> 00:24:20,790
how can Kai possibly win?

451
00:24:24,327 --> 00:24:25,428
That's weird.

452
00:24:25,428 --> 00:24:28,097
I can't picture how their
battle is going to end.

